caption: Awesome as usual! Like mom used to make.

We had an amazing experience here, it was an almost perfect stay as always. I would like to say that everyone was accommodating and helpful when we asked something needed. They also served a perfect food!
Been craving for ramen soup. Luckily I found this restaurant. I have been satisfied with the food that I ordered. Thank you so much guys!.
Excellent service great food..

I was a bit apprehensive about trying Danish food but I was pleasantly surprised how good the meatball sliders were. I rather have this than shake shack’s burger. And $3 mimosas - how can you go wrong.  We recently tried the pork belly and it’s delicious. Crunchy pork belly is so good with their home made gravy.
Fresh and delicious!
Such a Joy to find Taste of Denmark while on our Seven Bridges Tour!!

We had a super tasty Danish lunch at Taste of Denmark today!!! We haven’t tried Danish food before so it was our first time. The smoked salmon sandwich (on rye bread) tastes so fresh and good, so as the meat ball and fried fish sandwiches. …

True Danish. Rye bread like you find in Denmark, nothing like what we call rye bread. Delicious. Hot and cold smoked salmon dishes. The best red cabbage I've ever had. And you have to try a Danish hot dog! Meatballs in brown savory gravy …

Fantastic family owned company. We ordered their Christmas Eve feast which was such an easy process to coordinate with Tina. Everything arrived properly packaged and looks beautiful, it even came with heating instructions. Customer service …
Surely a place worth stopping over, the food is great and well prepared, the costs are fair and it is regularly well organized in here. Highly recommended.

two days ago was our first time we went to this good restaurant. But It is absolutely not the last time. We enjoyed the evening a lot with the efficient service, with the fine cooking and fine drinks and with the decent pay. We will no doubt go back there again.
Please, please. please visit this restaurant.  We need to support small independent eateries. The food is wonderful and will be a change of pace for everyone not currently living in Denmark
Everything was flavorful and  delicious, would definitely go again.
WOW! If you are a foodie this is a absolute must, owners with the most amazing positive energy and so nice, food quality way above competitors at this price level. Excellent spot for lunch.
Food was so good!
The smoke salmon was amazing. Would recommend this place to anyone who likes delicious food.

Visited Taste of Denmark for the first time today. The owner Tina was very welcoming and friendly. I am Danish myself and do go home every year, but it was an amazing experience having authentic and tasty Danish food while in San Diego. I …
Absolutely phenomenal and authentic restaurant owned by an absolutely lovely couple from Denmark. The Tartlet is an absolute must try!
This place was exceptional, from the service to the food everything was perfect!!! Give this small business your patronage!!!
The most authentic Danish restaurant in the SoCal area! Get the sausage, it is as authentic as the dogs in the stands in Copenhagen! The staff are very warm and welcoming. Tak!

We met with friends at this place for dinner. my friend recommended this restaurant.  Well, it was a winning. The crew welcomed us with a smile and we felt fantastic. The meal was great. We loved this place a lot and we will visit this place again. Highly recommended.
Easily one of the best chicken spots I've tried. Sauce and chicken sliders are bomb!

First visit. Food was excellent! Wife got Shoyu Ramen, great portion and delicious broth. I got the Chicken Don, chicken was tender and very tasty, also a great portion and I loved the pickled ginger. We will be back.

At the moment  you come to that restaurant  the waiters give you an excellent feeling. Very courteous waiters, it is a nice place to  pass time with friends or with your date. Excellent  meals, specialist  chef, competitive  price and generous  service. Highly recommended.
Authentic — and very tasty! — Danish food served up by friendly owners.
Very friendly service and authentic, tasty renditions of some tried and true Danish basics.
The food here is amazing and the staff is so friendly ! The meatball sliders were so good.
The customer service is constantly swift, good atmosphere, welcoming staff members. Will return here again when I am nearby.

As you probably already know I’m an explorer, well, in flavors too, and finding Taste of Denmark brought so much delicious taste to my journey. This family owned business is the cutest place. Small tables and comes this sweet Danish young …
Great food and fantastic service. Tina, one of the owners, is a phenomenal host and very accommodating. Did I mention the food was phenomenal?!

Wow! I have been to Denmark several times and I initially had some trepidation about coming to a Danish restaurant in San Diego - just like I might if I found a Mexican restaurant in Denmark (which I did). Anyhoo, the entire group and I …

San Diego how did you get so lucky. High quality at a fraction of the cost you would pay anywhere else for this experience. This restaurant really know what they are doing. The food here is divine, Danish meatballs! Go try it or you will regret it, might sound ordinary but it’s extraordinary.
Husband and I loved it. Delicious lunch with quick attentive owner. Thank you.
Small restaurant that does everything right! Love it. Waitress soooo sweet and the food is to die for.

Wonderfully fresh food and a little something different. Staff is amazingly nice and attentive. Fresh made blended drinks and a liquor license. If you're the type of person who gets meat balls from IKEA, then you need to come try the real …
So good! Just like my grandma's!

I wasn’t sure what I was getting myself into. Had the burger it was huge and I wasn’t even that hungry but couldn’t stop. the taste the texture, I was hooked. I have to come back and try more dishes next time I visit.

Phenomenal. I brought my friends here and they all loved it. Small restaurant with a delicious creative menu perfectly seasoned  everything spot on. I heard of this place only a couple of weeks ago. I guess it’s the place to be on sundays, it was pretty packed and still the service and food, you know where I am going it’s outstanding.
Delicious and such a quaint spot. Feels like you step into Europe for a bit. Good service and authentic food.
Best danishes found here! Like you get in Copenhagen. Beware small batches, they sell out quickly.
Such a delight. Delicious, authentic food and wonderful service!

Whoa! Didn't know this place existed until my date suggested it, I'm so glad I do now. If you love bacon, you've never had it prepared the way they do - it's amazing! That white gravy served with the potatoes and pork belly entree... Yes!!! …

My husband and me went to Copenhagen last month and we enjoyed very much their food. Today we discovered this gem here in our city. It was a fantastic adventure ! The food was authentic, delicious, well prepared and presented, like the …

What a delicious area! Filled with shade and also comfort. We ate like Danes. I have always intended to try pickled herring and this was my initial time. It was scrumptious! The owner (who came from Denmark a few years ago) was extremely pleasant and also really mindful) We will come once more next time we're around!
I love this bakery!!!!  The almond tarts and cinnamon bread are heavenly I could not get enough.  I even took some home with to AZ were it did not last a afternoon.

Wanted to do something different for Mother’s Day, found this place searching the web. The reviews were amazing and this place is in fact nothing short of amazing. Kids can be picky but not when visiting this place I have to say, they …
Healthy and tasty food done absolutely to perfection for a very good price.

Super cozy atmosphere, I went for the fried pork with parsley sauce and wifey had the tartlet so we could share a bit. I never been a fan of white asparagus, I am now! Adding another layer of umami. Pork and sauce delicious, but more than I …

Holy moly. YES!! Incredible job by the two owners, we loved every bite super delicious and well thought out menu. Restaurants like this is the reason to go out.. everything made from scratch. You can see, taste and smell it’s pure love. We …

Stopped by for lunch and had a wonderful meal.  The waitress was extremely attentive and very helpful.  The menu was small, only 8 items but everything we ate was done perfect and fresh.  Lunch times run 11-3 and dinner is 5-10.  So if you arrive around 4 they may not be open.  Strongly recommend supporting this local establishment.
Really excellent food and great atmosphere.
If you love Danish food -- or want a delicious introduction to the authentic thing, you must try this cute little place in Hillcrest. Lovely owners, fabulous menu.

The food is great! Especially the rye bread they give you as a little complimentary appetizer. We had the meatballs which were so flavorful. Oh and the pastries - yummmm. The place is owned by a young Danish couple who are so kind and lovely to chat with. Will definitely be back!
The food was so amazing and the customer support was out of this world I would completely recommend going here.

The service was very good and the food was outstanding Chicken pie is to die for. Cheap beer and mimosas Great place to hang out with friends or lunch date maybe They have decent outdoor seating for couples. First timers here but definitely not our last visit.
Sweet and fruity excellent rice pudding.
Great salmon. Nice Danish lady.
Delicious rye bread
Great place with something a little different

Danish food is the new black in the culinary world in case you missed it. I am so excited we have a taste of Denmark here in San Diego. The hostess will help you with choices if you wish and she is really good company. Great quality food, …
Very friendly staff. Ebelskiver was just like my mom's (and better than in Solvang!) Can't wait to go back and try the rest of their menu!

Love this place! The Danish rye bread is wonderful served with cabbage salad, goat cheese and another tangy spread. If you are a quality meatball fan this is the place to go, potato salad served with meatballs is also excellent. Chicken in …
The food is fantastic in this place! Worth the visit! Very simple and great quality!

This place is a little gem in Hillcrest. The owners are so nice and explain the menu. Everything is freshly prepared. Try the open faced sandwiches with their own freshly made bread. Delicious. I am from Germany and their bread is …
Great food and very friendly owners
Good authentic food.

So good it made my boyfriend cry! Do your tastebuds a favor and try it at least once!  This is not fast food. This is real home cooked food by a lovely couple from Denmark. They are so friendly, I felt right at home when I came in. They are just starting out so please support them...  The food really is delicious!!!

Very hospitable and a great change of pace from the usual Asian,  Mexican and Italian eateries.  The fruit/veggie juices are seriously tasty DIFFERENT,  no joke,  not the usual stuff.  The appetizer of rye bread,  goat cheese and pickled sweet cabbage was so nice.  Thank you , Taste of Denmark! Tak, Smag af Danmark!

Great food, especially the chicken tartlet but the other things are very good too. Run by a Danish couple, he in the kitchen and she serving in the restaurant so sometimes the wait can be slightly long, but worth waiting for, and the service is always very friendly and kind.
So good we didn't want to stop eating!   😍

Taste of Denmark serves authentic and delicious Danish lunch entrees. Our lunch entrees were preceded by an appetizer platter garnished with the best rye bread you can find in San Diego.  The hostess did a nice job explaining the appetizer …
Authentic Delicious Danish Food served by Friendly Folk!!

I normally don't write reviews however I had a fantastic Lunch at taste of Denmark. The food here is so delicious, desserts to die for. Friendly and attentive waitresss I would give her 5 stars 🌟alone. Highly recommend this place.
The meatballs were good but only two open faced sandwiches available .  The owner was lovely.   Think more authentic sandwiches would be great.  Good luck.  Tak for siste.
Food was delicious and the owner was very friendly!

I have always dreamed of going to the most friendliest country in the world; Denmark! I was delighted to the met the folks at this wonderful resturant, it is very clean, a cheerful atmosphere and beautifully decorated. Until I am in the country of Denmark, I will be here where the food is handmade.
